00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,919
It was a languid summer afternoon in Baker Street,

00:00:02,919 --> 00:00:06,820
the sort of afternoon where even the restless pulse of London

00:00:06,820 --> 00:00:09,470
seemed to falter beneath a golden haze.

00:00:09,470 --> 00:00:13,259
Holmes reclined upon the settee, long fingers steepled,

00:00:13,259 --> 00:00:17,190
his keen eyes half-lidded yet unmistakably alive with thought,

00:00:17,190 --> 00:00:20,679
while I sat opposite him attempting, with moderate success,

00:00:20,679 --> 00:00:23,399
to follow the tangled threads of his reasoning

00:00:23,399 --> 00:00:25,780
regarding a matter of trivial correspondence.

00:00:25,780 --> 00:00:39,500
My dear Watson, you persist in observing, but you do not yet see, and therein lies the gulf between us, though I assure you it is not an unbridgeable one.

00:00:39,500 --> 00:00:49,659
I confess, Holmes, that I saw nothing remarkable in the letter you examined so intently, aside from its somewhat hurried penmanship and the faint scent of lavender.

00:00:49,659 --> 00:01:14,980
Precisely, Watson, and yet you overlook the most telling details. The ink is of a rural make, not London manufacture. The lavender is not perfume but residue from pressed flowers, and the tremor in the strokes suggests not haste but fear restrained by deliberate composure.

00:01:14,980 --> 00:01:20,200
Before I could reply, Mrs. Hudson entered with her usual quiet efficiency,

00:01:20,200 --> 00:01:23,030
bearing a card upon a small silver tray.

00:01:23,030 --> 00:01:29,349
Her expression betraying just enough curiosity to suggest the visitor below was of uncommon distinction.

00:01:29,349 --> 00:01:32,620
A gentleman has called to see you, Mr. Holmes,

00:01:32,620 --> 00:01:38,680
and insists the matter is of utmost urgency and cannot be delayed.

00:01:38,680 --> 00:01:42,159
Show him up at once, Mrs. Hudson,

00:01:42,159 --> 00:01:46,959
for urgency is the very breath of our profession

00:01:46,959 --> 00:01:53,549
and I suspect this visitor carries more than mere concern upon his shoulders.

00:01:53,549 --> 00:01:57,379
Moments later, a tall pale gentleman entered the room,

00:01:57,379 --> 00:02:00,140
his coat marked with dust of a reddish hue,

00:02:00,140 --> 00:02:02,500
his boots worn yet carefully polished

00:02:02,500 --> 00:02:07,879
and his eyes darting with the restless agitation of one pursued by unseen anxieties.

00:02:07,879 --> 00:02:11,159
Mr. Holmes, I presume, for I have been told

00:02:11,159 --> 00:02:16,840
behold, there is no other man in England capable of unravelling such a perplexity as the one

00:02:16,840 --> 00:02:17,860
that has befallen me.

00:02:17,860 --> 00:02:24,319
You presume correctly, sir, and I observe that you have travelled from the countryside

00:02:24,319 --> 00:02:33,080
quite recently, most likely from a region with clay-rich soil and abundant wild roses,

00:02:33,080 --> 00:02:41,629
though I cannot yet determine why such a journey should distress you so profoundly.

00:02:41,629 --> 00:02:45,230
Your observation is nothing short of miraculous,

00:02:45,230 --> 00:02:47,979
for I have indeed come from Rosemond Valley

00:02:47,979 --> 00:02:53,900
and it is there that a most dreadful and inexplicable series of events has occurred.

00:02:53,900 --> 00:02:57,500
Holmes leaned forward with a sudden sharpening of interest,

00:02:57,500 --> 00:03:04,000
His languor vanishing entirely as if replaced by an electric current of intellectual excitement.

00:03:04,000 --> 00:03:12,959
Rosemond Valley, you say, a name that suggests beauty yet now carries the shadow of something darker.

00:03:12,959 --> 00:03:21,410
Pray continue, Mr. Ashcroft, and omit no detail, however trivial it may appear to you.

00:03:21,410 --> 00:03:30,449
The valley is my ancestral estate, a place of rolling hills and dense groves of wild roses that bloom even in the harshest conditions.

00:03:30,449 --> 00:03:37,240
But over the past fortnight, a series of occurrences has cast a pall upon the land and its inhabitants.

00:03:37,240 --> 00:03:45,340
I noted the trembling of his hands as he spoke, and though he strove for composure, his voice betrayed a deep and growing dread.

00:03:45,340 --> 00:03:49,329
It began with the disappearance of one of my groundskeepers,

00:03:49,329 --> 00:03:53,699
a loyal man who had served my family for years without incident

00:03:53,699 --> 00:03:58,920
and whose absence was at first attributed to desertion or misfortune.

00:03:58,920 --> 00:04:06,290
Disappearance is rarely as simple as it first appears, Mr. Ashcroft.

00:04:06,290 --> 00:04:10,430
For men do not vanish without leaving behind a trail,

00:04:10,430 --> 00:04:14,060
however faint, for those who know how to look.

00:04:14,060 --> 00:04:19,889
That is precisely the matter, Mr. Holmes, for there was no trail, no sign of struggle,

00:04:19,889 --> 00:04:25,569
no indication whatsoever of his fate, save for a single rose left upon his doorstep.

00:04:25,569 --> 00:04:28,990
Its petals stained a curious shade of crimson.

00:04:28,990 --> 00:04:34,199
Holmes's eyes gleamed with an intensity I had come to recognize as the harbinger

00:04:34,199 --> 00:04:36,980
of a case that would demand his full faculties.

00:04:36,980 --> 00:04:43,240
A rose, you say, left deliberately as a token or perhaps a warning.

00:04:43,240 --> 00:04:53,300
Though the coloration suggests either an artificial dye or a chemical reaction rather than natural pigmentation.

00:04:53,300 --> 00:04:54,439
..

00:04:54,439 --> 00:05:00,909
Since that first disappearance, two more individuals have vanished under similar circumstances,

00:05:00,909 --> 00:05:05,959
each preceded by the appearance of a rose unlike any that grows in the valley.

00:05:05,959 --> 00:05:13,379
I could not help but feel a chill at his words, for there was something almost ritualistic in the pattern he described.

00:05:13,379 --> 00:05:14,959
..

00:05:14,959 --> 00:05:27,379
Patterns, Mr. Ashcroft, are the language of intention, and intention is the key to understanding any crime, no matter how elaborate or concealed.

00:05:27,379 --> 00:05:35,100
There is more, Mr. Holmes, for on the night before each disappearance, strange lights have been seen upon the hills.

00:05:35,100 --> 00:05:38,040
accompanied by a low, mournful sound

00:05:38,040 --> 00:05:41,769
that some have likened to a voice carried upon the wind.

00:05:41,769 --> 00:05:46,029
Holmes rose abruptly, crossing the room with swift, decisive steps,

00:05:46,029 --> 00:05:49,899
his mind clearly racing ahead of the facts already presented.

00:05:49,899 --> 00:05:54,700
You have done wisely to come to me, Mr. Ashcroft.

00:05:54,700 --> 00:06:01,540
For this matter bears all the hallmarks of design rather than superstition,

00:06:01,540 --> 00:06:10,930
though I shall not discount the psychological influence of fear upon those who witness such phenomena.

00:06:10,930 --> 00:06:14,419
Then you will come to Rosemond Valley, Mr. Holmes,

00:06:14,419 --> 00:06:20,700
for I fear that if these events continue unchecked, no one within the estate will be safe.

00:06:20,700 --> 00:06:25,620
My dear sir, I would not miss such an opportunity for the world,

00:06:25,620 --> 00:06:29,980
for it is not often that a case presents itself

00:06:29,980 --> 00:06:37,100
with such a curious blend of natural beauty and underlying menace.

00:06:37,100 --> 00:06:40,600
Holmes turned to me with that familiar spark in his eyes,

00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:44,509
the one that invariably preceded our most memorable adventures.

00:06:44,509 --> 00:06:49,000
Watson, you will accompany me, of course,

00:06:49,000 --> 00:06:51,379
for your presence is indispensable,

00:06:51,379 --> 00:07:00,379
both as a chronicler of events and as a steadying influence upon my more experimental inclinations.

00:07:00,379 --> 00:07:06,399
I should be delighted, Holmes, for I sense that this case will provide ample opportunity for me

00:07:06,399 --> 00:07:10,540
to further my understanding of your remarkable methods of deduction.

00:07:10,540 --> 00:07:16,339
Then it is settled, and we shall depart for Rosemont Valley

00:07:16,339 --> 00:07:21,149
at the earliest possible moment, for time as ever.

00:07:21,149 --> 00:07:25,500
is the one adversary we cannot afford to underestimate.

00:07:25,500 --> 00:07:26,740
..

00:07:26,740 --> 00:07:31,490
As preparations were made and our visitor departed with a measure of renewed hope,

00:07:31,490 --> 00:07:37,149
I could not help but reflect upon the strange nature of the case that lay before us,

00:07:37,149 --> 00:07:41,920
for it seemed to straddle the boundary between the rational and the inexplicable.

00:07:41,920 --> 00:07:48,040
Little did I know that the journey to Rosemond Valley would lead us into a labyrinth of secrets,

00:07:48,040 --> 00:07:53,899
where beauty masked danger, and where even the keen intellect of Sherlock Holmes would be tested

00:07:53,899 --> 00:07:59,899
in ways neither of us could yet imagine. Our journey from London to Rosemont Valley commenced

00:07:59,899 --> 00:08:05,779
under a sky of pale silver, the early morning mist clinging to the countryside like a ghost

00:08:05,779 --> 00:08:12,180
reluctant to depart. Holmes remained unusually silent throughout the train ride, his long frame

00:08:12,180 --> 00:08:17,819
folded into the corner of the carriage, eyes fixed not upon the passing scenery, but upon the

00:08:17,819 --> 00:08:26,059
interior landscape of his own formidable mind. Watson, you observe the countryside as picturesque,

00:08:26,059 --> 00:08:32,379
yet you fail to consider how isolation breeds opportunity, and how opportunity,

00:08:32,379 --> 00:08:39,740
when combined with intent, gives rise to the most curious forms of crime.

00:08:39,740 --> 00:08:45,820
I concede, Holmes, that my attention is more readily drawn to the beauty of the rolling hills

00:08:45,820 --> 00:08:48,769
than to the darker possibilities they may conceal,

00:08:48,769 --> 00:08:53,129
though I shall endeavor to refine my perspective under your guidance.

00:08:53,129 --> 00:08:58,039
It is not beauty that deceives, my dear Watson,

00:08:58,039 --> 00:09:02,159
but our willingness to accept it at face value

00:09:02,159 --> 00:09:06,450
without probing the mechanisms that sustain it.

00:09:06,450 --> 00:09:11,220
By the time we reached the small rural station nearest to Rosemont Valley,

00:09:11,220 --> 00:09:14,200
the sun had risen high enough to burn away the mist,

00:09:14,200 --> 00:09:16,990
revealing a landscape of extraordinary charm,

00:09:16,990 --> 00:09:21,799
dotted with cottages and framed by distant hills covered in dense vegetation.

00:09:21,799 --> 00:09:22,899
..

00:09:22,899 --> 00:09:25,039
Mr. Holmes, Dr. Watson,

00:09:25,039 --> 00:09:28,430
I am relieved beyond measure to see you have arrived safely,

00:09:28,430 --> 00:09:32,500
for matters at the estate have grown no less troubling in your absence.

00:09:32,500 --> 00:09:33,560
..

00:09:33,560 --> 00:09:37,470
Your anxiety is evident, Mr. Ashcroft,

00:09:37,470 --> 00:09:41,860
though I note with interest that you have not slept well

00:09:41,860 --> 00:09:49,250
and that your boots carry fresh traces of the same reddish clay we observed previously,

00:09:49,250 --> 00:09:55,480
suggesting you have been walking the grounds at unusual hours.

00:09:55,480 --> 00:10:01,660
You are quite correct, Mr. Holmes, for I have scarcely slept these past nights,

00:10:01,660 --> 00:10:08,440
choosing instead to patrol the estate in hopes of catching some sign of the force behind these dreadful events.

00:10:08,440 --> 00:10:14,899
We were soon conveyed by carriage along a winding road that descended into the valley itself,

00:10:14,899 --> 00:10:19,559
and I must confess that the sight which greeted us was one of haunting beauty,

00:10:19,559 --> 00:10:23,720
for the valley was indeed filled with wild roses of every hue,

00:10:23,720 --> 00:10:26,179
their fragrance carried upon a gentle breeze.

00:10:26,179 --> 00:10:28,220
...

00:10:28,220 --> 00:10:32,819
Remarkable, Watson. Observe the density of the rose growth,

00:10:32,819 --> 00:10:37,320
and note how it forms natural corridors through the valley,

00:10:37,320 --> 00:10:45,370
which could serve as both concealment and pathway for anyone familiar with the terrain.

00:10:45,370 --> 00:10:47,289
I see what you mean, Holmes.

00:10:47,289 --> 00:10:53,309
Though I should not have thought such natural formations could play a role in a criminal enterprise.

00:10:53,309 --> 00:10:58,220
That, Watson, is precisely why they are so effective.

00:10:58,220 --> 00:10:59,260
..

00:10:59,260 --> 00:11:05,440
For nature provides the perfect disguise for artifice when employed with sufficient cunning.

00:11:05,440 --> 00:11:11,840
The manor house itself stood upon a gentle rise, its stone walls weathered yet imposing,

00:11:11,840 --> 00:11:18,069
with tall windows that seemed to gaze out upon the valley with a watchful, almost sentient presence.

00:11:18,069 --> 00:11:25,080
Welcome, Mr. Holmes and Dr. Watson. I trust your journey was not too taxing,

00:11:25,080 --> 00:11:30,960
though I fear the circumstances of your visit are far from pleasant.

00:11:30,960 --> 00:11:44,950
We are accustomed to unpleasant circumstances, madam, for they often yield the most illuminating truths, provided one is willing to look beyond appearances.

00:11:44,950 --> 00:11:56,340
Mrs. Dalrymple, the housekeeper, possessed a composed demeanor, yet there was an undercurrent of unease in her voice that spoke volumes about the atmosphere within the household.

00:11:56,340 --> 00:12:12,500
If you will follow me, gentlemen, I shall show you to your rooms, after which Mr. Ashcroft has arranged for you to inspect the grounds where the last disappearance occurred.

00:12:12,500 --> 00:12:23,620
Holmes nodded curtly, his attention already drifting toward the windows that overlooked the valley, as though he sought to absorb every detail before even setting foot outside.

00:12:23,620 --> 00:12:31,960
side. Watson, note the orientation of the house relative to the valley and consider how sound

00:12:31,960 --> 00:12:40,329
might travel across such terrain, particularly at night when the air is cooler and denser.

00:12:40,329 --> 00:12:45,940
You believe then that the strange sounds reported by Mr. Ashcroft have a natural explanation

00:12:45,940 --> 00:12:48,240
rather than a supernatural one.

00:12:48,240 --> 00:12:51,710
I believe nothing, Watson,

00:12:51,710 --> 00:12:56,349
until I have sufficient evidence to support a conclusion.

00:12:56,349 --> 00:13:01,019
Though I admit that nature often provides explanations

00:13:01,019 --> 00:13:05,849
that appear supernatural to the untrained observer.

00:13:05,849 --> 00:13:09,620
After a brief respite, we accompanied Mr. Ashcroft

00:13:09,620 --> 00:13:11,759
to the site of the most recent disappearance,

00:13:11,759 --> 00:13:16,039
a small cottage situated at the edge of a dense thicket of roses,

00:13:16,039 --> 00:13:20,980
their petals forming a vivid tapestry of colour against the green foliage.

00:13:20,980 --> 00:13:24,240
This is where the last man was taken, Mr. Holmes,

00:13:24,240 --> 00:13:26,980
and as before, there was no sign of struggle,

00:13:26,980 --> 00:13:29,480
no indication of what befell him,

00:13:29,480 --> 00:13:32,089
only the presence of that cursed rose.

00:13:32,089 --> 00:13:36,779
May I see the rose in question, if it has been preserved,

00:13:36,779 --> 00:13:43,059
for such an object may hold the key to understanding the entire affair.

00:13:43,059 --> 00:13:44,639
..

00:13:44,639 --> 00:13:49,909
Indeed, I anticipated your request, and have kept it carefully stored within the manor,

00:13:49,909 --> 00:13:53,980
though I must warn you that its appearance is most unsettling.

00:13:53,980 --> 00:13:59,250
Holmes crouched near the doorway of the cottage, examining the ground with meticulous care,

00:13:59,250 --> 00:14:05,059
his fingers brushing aside loose soil as his eyes scanned for the faintest irregularity.

00:14:05,059 --> 00:14:24,980
Watson observes this indentation barely visible to the naked eye, yet unmistakably the impression of a narrow boot, likely belonging to a man of slight build, who approached from the direction of the rose thicket.

00:14:24,980 --> 00:14:30,590
Extraordinary, Holmes, for I should never have noticed such a detail without your guidance,

00:14:30,590 --> 00:14:35,600
though I must ask how you distinguish this from the many other marks upon the ground.

00:14:35,600 --> 00:14:44,750
It is a matter of contrast, Watson, for the soil here is disturbed in a manner inconsistent

00:14:44,750 --> 00:14:51,799
with natural movement, suggesting deliberate placement of weight rather than the random

00:14:51,799 --> 00:14:58,690
patterns left by animals or wind. Holmes then rose and moved toward the thicket itself,

00:14:58,690 --> 00:15:05,360
parting the branches with surprising delicacy, as though he feared disturbing some hidden mechanism.

00:15:05,360 --> 00:15:13,860
Ah, as I suspected, there is a narrow path concealed within the roses, scarcely visible,

00:15:13,860 --> 00:15:20,590
unless one knows precisely where to look and leading deeper into the valley.

00:15:20,590 --> 00:15:29,109
I had no knowledge of such a path, Mr. Holmes, for I have walked these grounds countless times and never once encountered it.

00:15:29,109 --> 00:15:41,120
That, Mr. Ashcroft, is precisely the point, for the most effective paths are those that remain unseen by those who do not require them.

00:15:41,120 --> 00:15:50,960
A faint unease settled upon me as I gazed into the shadowed passage, for it seemed to beckon with a silent promise of secrets best left undisturbed.

00:15:50,960 --> 00:16:07,899
Watson, we shall follow this path, for it is here that the truth begins to reveal itself, though we must proceed with caution, as the architect of this design is clearly both methodical and patient.

00:16:07,899 --> 00:16:14,700
Very well, Holmes, though I cannot deny a certain apprehension at what we may discover beyond those roses.

00:16:14,700 --> 00:16:15,739
..

00:16:15,739 --> 00:16:25,899
Apprehension is a natural response, Watson, but it must never be allowed to interfere with the pursuit of knowledge,

00:16:25,899 --> 00:16:31,200
for it is only through understanding that we may dispel fear.

00:16:31,200 --> 00:16:35,990
Together, we stepped into the narrow corridor formed by the roses,

00:16:35,990 --> 00:16:39,079
their branches closing behind us like a curtain,

00:16:39,079 --> 00:16:42,100
as though we were crossing a threshold into a realm

00:16:42,100 --> 00:16:45,700
where logic and mystery intertwined in equal measure.

00:16:45,700 --> 00:16:51,230
It was at that moment, as the light dimmed and the air grew heavy with the scent of blossoms,

00:16:51,230 --> 00:16:54,419
that I realized our investigation had truly begun

00:16:54,419 --> 00:16:59,559
and that Rosemond Valley held secrets far deeper than any of us had yet imagined.

00:16:59,559 --> 00:17:16,039
The moment we crossed into the concealed passage within the rose thicket, I felt as though we had stepped into an entirely different world, one where the cheerful vitality of the valley gave way to a hushed and oppressive stillness that weighed heavily upon the senses.

00:17:16,039 --> 00:17:23,380
You perceive the change, Watson, not merely in light but in sound.

00:17:23,380 --> 00:17:31,039
For the density of these roses absorbs is and distorts the natural acoustics,

00:17:31,039 --> 00:17:36,710
creating an environment where even the faintest movement becomes significant.

00:17:36,710 --> 00:17:40,619
Indeed, Holmes, the silence here is of a peculiar quality,

00:17:40,619 --> 00:17:43,220
as though the air itself were listening

00:17:43,220 --> 00:17:48,349
and I cannot help but feel that we are intruding upon something carefully concealed.

00:17:48,349 --> 00:17:50,640
An excellent observation, Watson.

00:17:50,640 --> 00:17:51,839
..

00:17:51,839 --> 00:17:55,619
For concealment is the very essence of this arrangement

00:17:55,619 --> 00:18:00,740
and we must assume that whoever constructed this path

00:18:00,740 --> 00:18:04,400
did so with both intention and precision.

00:18:04,400 --> 00:18:05,579
..

00:18:05,579 --> 00:18:09,920
The path wound its way through the dense foliage in a series of subtle turns,

00:18:09,920 --> 00:18:15,099
each one obscuring the next until the manor house was entirely lost from view

00:18:15,099 --> 00:18:18,920
and the valley beyond reduced to little more than a distant memory.

00:18:18,920 --> 00:18:23,410
Note the regularity of the turns, Watson,

00:18:23,410 --> 00:18:30,650
which suggests deliberate planning rather than natural growth,

00:18:30,650 --> 00:18:34,660
as well as the careful pruning of branches at shoulder height,

00:18:34,660 --> 00:18:40,700
indicating frequent passage by an individual of consistent stature.

00:18:40,700 --> 00:18:41,740
..

00:18:41,740 --> 00:18:45,860
Your attention to such minute details continues to astonish me, Holmes,

00:18:45,860 --> 00:18:49,440
for I should never have considered that the very shape of a branch

00:18:49,440 --> 00:18:52,599
might reveal the habits of a hidden intruder.

00:18:52,599 --> 00:18:59,260
There is nothing so trivial that it cannot become significant, Watson,

00:18:59,260 --> 00:19:03,700
provided one examines it within the proper context

00:19:03,700 --> 00:19:08,509
and with the appropriate degree of skepticism.

00:19:08,509 --> 00:19:11,800
As we proceeded further, the air grew cooler,

00:19:11,800 --> 00:19:15,659
and a faint metallic scent began to mingle with the fragrance of the roses,

00:19:15,659 --> 00:19:19,289
a scent that stirred an uneasy familiarity within me.

00:19:19,289 --> 00:19:22,660
You detect it as well, Watson,

00:19:22,660 --> 00:19:28,529
the subtle tang of iron which suggests the presence of blood,

00:19:28,529 --> 00:19:30,819
though not necessarily recent,

00:19:30,819 --> 00:19:36,660
and certainly not in a quantity that would immediately betray its source.

00:19:36,660 --> 00:19:37,939
..

00:19:37,939 --> 00:19:39,940
The implication sent a chill through me

00:19:39,940 --> 00:19:43,460
and I found myself gripping my walking stick more tightly

00:19:43,460 --> 00:19:48,130
as though it might offer some measure of protection against the unknown.

00:19:48,130 --> 00:19:54,440
Courage, my dear Watson, for while danger may indeed be present,

00:19:54,440 --> 00:20:00,339
it is the unseen danger that most often proves illusory.

00:20:00,339 --> 00:20:18,619
whereas that which leaves traces may be understood and therefore countered at length the path opened into a small clearing and there upon a flat stone at its centre lay a single rose its petals of a deep and unnatural crimson that seemed to absorb the very light around it

00:20:18,619 --> 00:20:25,119
Good heavens! It is another of those dreadful flowers, identical to the ones found at the

00:20:25,119 --> 00:20:30,799
sites of the disappearances, and yet how it came to be here I cannot begin to imagine.

00:20:30,799 --> 00:20:38,170
Pray do not touch it, Mr. Ashcroft, for such objects are often more than they appear,

00:20:38,170 --> 00:20:42,690
and may serve purposes beyond mere symbolism.

00:20:42,690 --> 00:20:45,839
Holmes approached the stone with measured steps,

00:20:45,839 --> 00:20:50,599
His gaze fixed upon the rose as though it were a puzzle waiting to be solved.

00:20:50,599 --> 00:20:51,619
..

00:20:51,619 --> 00:20:56,940
Observe, Watson, the uniformity of the coloration,

00:20:56,940 --> 00:21:01,400
which lacks the subtle variation found in natural petals,

00:21:01,400 --> 00:21:02,500
..

00:21:02,500 --> 00:21:05,630
as well as the slight residue upon the stone,

00:21:05,630 --> 00:21:09,509
which suggests the application of a liquid agent.

00:21:09,509 --> 00:21:13,900
You believe, then, that the color is artificially produced, Holmes,

00:21:13,900 --> 00:21:17,300
rather than a natural characteristic of the flower.

00:21:17,300 --> 00:21:22,460
Beyond any reasonable doubt, Watson, for nature,

00:21:22,460 --> 00:21:25,259
though capable of remarkable variation,

00:21:25,259 --> 00:21:30,940
does not produce such consistency without external influence,

00:21:30,940 --> 00:21:34,740
particularly in a wild environment such as this.

00:21:34,740 --> 00:21:35,800
..

00:21:35,800 --> 00:21:38,019
Holmes produced a small lens from his pocket

00:21:38,019 --> 00:21:40,900
and examined the petals with intense concentration,

00:21:40,900 --> 00:21:45,700
His expression gradually shifting from curiosity to quiet satisfaction.

00:21:45,700 --> 00:21:46,880
..

00:21:46,880 --> 00:21:52,359
As I suspected, the petals have been treated with a chemical solution,

00:21:52,359 --> 00:21:53,460
..

00:21:53,460 --> 00:21:55,859
likely containing iron compounds,

00:21:55,859 --> 00:21:56,960
..

00:21:56,960 --> 00:22:03,980
which would account for both the coloration and the metallic scent we detected earlier.

00:22:03,980 --> 00:22:06,500
But to what end, Mr. Holmes?

00:22:06,500 --> 00:22:10,590
For what purpose could such a macabre display possibly serve?

00:22:10,590 --> 00:22:17,980
That, Mr. Ashcroft, is the question that lies at the heart of this mystery,

00:22:17,980 --> 00:22:22,440
and one that we are now considerably closer to answering.

00:22:22,440 --> 00:22:25,960
At that moment, a faint sound reached our ears,

00:22:25,960 --> 00:22:31,139
a low, mournful note that seemed to drift through the clearing like a distant lament.

00:22:31,139 --> 00:22:37,050
There it is again, that dreadful sound which has haunted the valley these past nights,

00:22:37,050 --> 00:22:39,720
and which no one has been able to explain.

00:22:39,720 --> 00:22:49,619
Remain calm, both of you, and attend closely, for the direction and quality of the sound may reveal its origin.

00:22:49,619 --> 00:22:50,620
..

00:22:50,620 --> 00:22:58,430
We stood in silence, straining to discern the source of the eerie noise, which seemed to rise and fall with an almost rhythmic pattern.

00:22:58,430 --> 00:23:09,369
Ah, how instructive, Watson, for the sound is not random, but rather the result of air passing through a narrow aperture.

00:23:09,369 --> 00:23:15,509
likely created by some form of concealed apparatus within the valley.

00:23:15,509 --> 00:23:18,940
You mean to say that the sound is artificial, Holmes,

00:23:18,940 --> 00:23:22,579
rather than some natural phenomenon or supernatural occurrence?

00:23:22,579 --> 00:23:23,660
..

00:23:23,660 --> 00:23:25,740
Precisely, Watson.

00:23:25,740 --> 00:23:29,569
For while it mimics the qualities of a natural sound,

00:23:29,569 --> 00:23:33,779
its regularity betrays the hand of human design

00:23:33,779 --> 00:23:38,759
and suggests that it is intended to evoke fear

00:23:38,759 --> 00:23:40,819
rather than convey meaning.

00:23:40,819 --> 00:23:41,839
..

00:23:41,839 --> 00:23:43,990
Holmes moved toward the edge of the clearing,

00:23:43,990 --> 00:23:48,639
his eyes scanning the surrounding foliage with renewed intensity.

00:23:48,639 --> 00:23:54,469
There, Watson, do you see that slight depression in the ground,

00:23:54,469 --> 00:23:57,639
partially concealed by fallen leaves,

00:23:57,639 --> 00:24:02,599
which indicates the presence of a hollow space beneath the surface?

00:24:02,599 --> 00:24:07,200
I do indeed, Holmes, though I should not have noticed it without your direction,

00:24:07,200 --> 00:24:09,579
for it is most cleverly hidden.

00:24:09,579 --> 00:24:15,199
It is the hallmark of an intelligent adversary, Watson,

00:24:15,199 --> 00:24:19,569
to conceal their mechanisms in plain sight,

00:24:19,569 --> 00:24:25,460
relying upon the inattentiveness of others to preserve their secrecy.

00:24:25,460 --> 00:24:26,620
..

00:24:26,620 --> 00:24:27,969
Do you suppose, Mr. Holmes,

00:24:27,969 --> 00:24:31,500
that this hollow space is connected to the disappearances

00:24:31,500 --> 00:24:35,180
and that it may conceal some form of entrance or passage?

00:24:35,180 --> 00:24:44,259
I should be very much surprised if it did not, Mr. Ashcroft, for the evidence thus far

00:24:44,259 --> 00:24:53,630
points to a carefully orchestrated system of movement and concealment beneath the very surface of your estate.

00:24:53,630 --> 00:24:58,320
Holmes knelt beside the depression and began to clear away the leaves,

00:24:58,320 --> 00:25:01,960
revealing a narrow wooden panel set flush with the ground,

00:25:01,960 --> 00:25:06,950
its edges so skillfully disguised that it would have escaped notice entirely.

00:25:06,950 --> 00:25:11,269
Watson, assist me in lifting this panel,

00:25:11,269 --> 00:25:17,610
for I believe we are about to uncover a most significant element of this mystery.

00:25:17,610 --> 00:25:20,530
With some effort, we pried the panel open,

00:25:20,530 --> 00:25:23,699
revealing a dark shaft that descended into the earth,

00:25:23,699 --> 00:25:27,700
from which the mournful sound seemed to emanate with greater clarity.

00:25:27,700 --> 00:25:37,190
Good Lord! I had no idea such a thing existed upon my land, for this suggests a level of intrusion far beyond anything I had imagined.

00:25:37,190 --> 00:25:52,779
Your ignorance, Mr. Ashcroft, is precisely what has enabled this operation to continue unchecked, though I do not say this as a reproach, but rather as a statement of fact.

00:25:52,779 --> 00:25:59,660
I peered into the darkness below, my heart pounding with a mixture of apprehension and anticipation.

00:25:59,660 --> 00:26:03,440
Holmes, do you intend that we descend into this passage?

00:26:03,440 --> 00:26:07,039
For I must admit that the prospect is not an inviting one.

00:26:07,039 --> 00:26:13,110
My dear Watson, when the path to truth leads downward into darkness,

00:26:13,110 --> 00:26:18,880
it is our duty to follow it, for it is only by confronting the unknown

00:26:18,880 --> 00:26:21,440
that we may bring it into the light.

00:26:21,440 --> 00:26:29,539
Holmes produced a lantern from his bag, its steady glow casting long shadows as he prepared to descend into the hidden passage.

00:26:29,539 --> 00:26:31,000
..

00:26:31,000 --> 00:26:44,139
Stay close, Watson, and remain alert, for while we pursue knowledge, we must not forget that we may also be approaching the architect of this elaborate design.

00:26:44,139 --> 00:26:51,309
With that, Holmes began his descent into the darkness, and I, gathering my resolve, followed close behind.

00:26:51,309 --> 00:26:55,000
knowing that whatever lay below would bring us closer to the truth

00:26:55,000 --> 00:26:58,210
but perhaps at a cost we had yet to comprehend.

00:26:58,210 --> 00:27:00,299
The descent into the hidden shaft

00:27:00,299 --> 00:27:04,200
was one of the most unsettling experiences of my life

00:27:04,200 --> 00:27:07,160
for the narrow wooden ladder creaked beneath our weight

00:27:07,160 --> 00:27:09,440
and the faint glow of Holmes' lantern

00:27:09,440 --> 00:27:12,980
seemed scarcely sufficient to pierce the oppressive darkness

00:27:12,980 --> 00:27:15,730
that enveloped us on all sides.

00:27:15,730 --> 00:27:17,059
Steady.

00:27:17,059 --> 00:27:19,200
Watson for the construction

00:27:19,200 --> 00:27:20,920
though concealed

00:27:20,920 --> 00:27:28,140
is sound enough and the spacing of the rungs suggests it was built by someone

00:27:28,140 --> 00:27:34,019
with both practical skill and an understanding of engineering principles.

00:27:34,019 --> 00:27:35,400
..

00:27:35,400 --> 00:27:39,190
Your composure in such circumstances never ceases to amaze me, Holmes,

00:27:39,190 --> 00:27:42,809
for I find myself acutely aware of every sound and shadow,

00:27:42,809 --> 00:27:46,240
each one suggesting dangers that may or may not exist.

00:27:46,240 --> 00:27:58,309
That awareness, Watson, is not a weakness but a resource, provided it is guided by reason rather than allowed to descend into panic.

00:27:58,309 --> 00:28:10,099
At last we reached the bottom, where the ladder gave way to a narrow earthen passage reinforced with wooden beams, their surfaces worn smooth by repeated contact, indicating frequent use.

00:28:10,099 --> 00:28:29,759
Observe, Watson, the marks upon these beams which are consistent with the passage of crates or equipment, suggesting that this tunnel serves not merely as a hiding place, but as a conduit for some ongoing operation.

00:28:29,759 --> 00:28:41,990
I see the abrasions you refer to, Holmes, though I should not have guessed their significance without your explanation, for they appear at first glance to be little more than natural wear.

00:28:41,990 --> 00:28:55,779
It is precisely in such distinctions that the truth resides, Watson, for nature rarely produces patterns of such regularity without human intervention.

00:28:55,779 --> 00:29:08,119
The air within the tunnel was heavy and tinged with the same metallic scent we had encountered above, now far stronger, mingled with the faint odor of chemicals that stung the nostrils.

00:29:08,119 --> 00:29:21,700
The presence of chemical vapors confirms my earlier hypothesis, Watson, that the roses are being treated with a compound, likely prepared within this very passage.

00:29:21,700 --> 00:29:28,730
As we advanced, the tunnel widened slightly, revealing a series of alcoves carved into the earth,

00:29:28,730 --> 00:29:36,930
within which were placed various implements, glass bottles and curious instruments whose purpose I could not immediately discern.

00:29:36,930 --> 00:29:45,440
Holmes, these apparatuses resemble those of a laboratory, though I cannot imagine why such a facility would be hidden beneath the estate.

00:29:45,440 --> 00:30:05,200
On the contrary, Watson, it is precisely the sort of location one would choose for clandestine experimentation, particularly if one wished to avoid scrutiny while conducting activities of a questionable nature.

00:30:05,200 --> 00:30:16,519
At that moment, a faint echo reached our ears. The same mournful sound we had heard above, now amplified within the confines of the tunnel, its source seemingly close at hand.

00:30:16,519 --> 00:30:25,440
Good heavens! The sound is far more pronounced here. And I cannot shake the feeling that we are being watched, though I see no one.

00:30:25,440 --> 00:30:38,570
Your unease is understandable, Mr. Ashcroft, though I assure you that the source of the sound is mechanical rather than supernatural, and we shall soon locate it.

00:30:38,570 --> 00:30:47,819
Holmes moved swiftly ahead, his lantern casting flickering shadows upon the walls as he followed the direction of the sound with unerring precision.

00:30:47,819 --> 00:30:55,900
There, Watson observed the aperture in the wall fitted with a series of narrow pipes

00:30:55,900 --> 00:31:04,660
through which air is being forced, producing the very sound that has so unnerved the inhabitants

00:31:04,660 --> 00:31:06,059
of the valley.

00:31:06,059 --> 00:31:11,400
Remarkable, Holmes, for the effect is indeed uncanny, and I can readily understand

00:31:11,400 --> 00:31:14,700
how it might be mistaken for something otherworldly.

00:31:14,700 --> 00:31:27,519
Precisely, Watson, and such misinterpretation is undoubtedly the intention, for fear is a most effective means of discouraging inquiry.

00:31:27,519 --> 00:31:37,259
As Holmes examined the apparatus, I became aware of another presence within the tunnel, a subtle shift in the air that suggested we were no longer alone.

00:31:37,259 --> 00:31:44,799
Holmes, did you hear that? For I could swear there was movement further along the passage, though I cannot be certain.

00:31:44,799 --> 00:31:46,099
..

00:31:46,099 --> 00:31:58,579
Your instincts serve you well, Watson, for I too have detected a disturbance, and it would appear that our investigations have not gone unnoticed.

00:31:58,579 --> 00:32:03,360
Before we could proceed further, a figure emerged from the shadows ahead,

00:32:03,360 --> 00:32:06,230
his face partially obscured by the dim light,

00:32:06,230 --> 00:32:10,599
yet his posture conveyed a curious mixture of confidence and agitation.

00:32:10,599 --> 00:32:11,759
..

00:32:11,759 --> 00:32:14,809
I must commend you, Mr. Holmes, for your ingenuity,

00:32:14,809 --> 00:32:18,720
though I regret that your interference has brought you to a place

00:32:18,720 --> 00:32:21,450
from which you may not easily depart.

00:32:21,450 --> 00:32:23,119
Who are you, sir?

00:32:23,119 --> 00:32:26,119
And by what right do you trespass beneath my estate

00:32:26,119 --> 00:32:28,619
state and perpetrate such monstrous deeds.

00:32:28,619 --> 00:32:29,799
..

00:32:29,799 --> 00:32:33,519
My name is of little consequence, though you may call me Dr. Ellison.

00:32:33,519 --> 00:32:39,980
And as for my right, I assure you that necessity and intellect have granted me far more authority

00:32:39,980 --> 00:32:42,809
than any inherited title ever could.

00:32:42,809 --> 00:32:50,400
Dr. Ellison, your methods betray a mind of considerable ability, though one that has

00:32:50,400 --> 00:32:58,809
chosen a most unfortunate path, for your elaborate contrivances cannot conceal the fundamental

00:32:58,809 --> 00:33:01,579
flaws in your design.

00:33:01,579 --> 00:33:07,559
Flaws, Mr. Holmes, I should be most interested to hear you elaborate, for I have taken great

00:33:07,559 --> 00:33:12,029
care to ensure that my work remains undetected and unchallenged.

00:33:12,029 --> 00:33:20,059
And yet here we stand, Dr. Ellison, having traced your operation from the roses above

00:33:20,059 --> 00:33:27,970
to the tunnels below, guided by the very clues you believed would deter investigation.

00:33:27,970 --> 00:33:32,819
The man's expression hardened, though there was a flicker of unease in his eyes

00:33:32,819 --> 00:33:38,599
that suggested Holmes' words had struck closer to the truth than he cared to admit.

00:33:38,599 --> 00:33:43,000
You have indeed uncovered a portion of my work, Mr. Holmes,

00:33:43,000 --> 00:33:48,220
but you cannot possibly comprehend its full scope, nor the necessity that drives it.

00:33:48,220 --> 00:33:56,179
On the contrary, Dr. Ellison, I believe I understand far more than you suppose,

00:33:56,179 --> 00:33:59,900
including the purpose of your chemical treatments

00:33:59,900 --> 00:34:05,440
and the role of the unfortunate individuals who have disappeared.

00:34:05,440 --> 00:34:10,179
A tense silence followed, broken only by the faint hum of the apparatus

00:34:10,179 --> 00:34:13,110
and the distant echo of the mournful sound.

00:34:13,110 --> 00:34:15,820
You speak of those men, Mr. Holmes.

00:34:15,820 --> 00:34:32,880
homes pray tell me they are not beyond saving for i cannot bear the thought that they have come to harm that mr ashcroft is a matter we shall soon determine though i fear the answer may not be entirely reassuring

00:34:32,880 --> 00:34:43,559
you presume too much mr holmes for while you have uncovered my sanctuary you have yet to grasp the true nature of my work or the consequences of your intrusion

00:34:43,559 --> 00:34:57,720
Then enlighten us, Dr. Ellison, for I find that even the most misguided intellect often reveals its intentions when given the opportunity to speak.

00:34:57,720 --> 00:35:04,460
The man hesitated, as though weighing his options, before a faint, almost defiant smile crossed his lips.

00:35:04,460 --> 00:35:05,559
..

00:35:05,559 --> 00:35:09,650
Very well, Mr. Holmes. If you are determined to understand,

00:35:09,650 --> 00:35:14,659
then you shall, though I suspect the knowledge may prove more troubling than ignorance.

00:35:14,659 --> 00:35:20,300
As he spoke, I could not help but feel that we stood upon the brink of a revelation that

00:35:20,300 --> 00:35:25,349
would cast the entire mystery of Rosemond Valley in a new and unsettling light.

00:35:25,349 --> 00:35:31,139
The dim glow of Holmes' lantern cast long and wavering shadows upon the earthen walls.

00:35:31,139 --> 00:35:36,880
As the figure of Dr. Ellison stood before us, his expression illuminated in fragments,

00:35:36,880 --> 00:35:41,539
revealing a man both brilliant and profoundly disturbed by the path he had chosen.

00:35:41,539 --> 00:35:54,340
.............

00:35:54,340 --> 00:35:58,219
Necessity is a word often invoked to justify actions

00:35:58,219 --> 00:36:03,819
that would otherwise be deemed indefensible, Dr. Ellison.

00:36:03,819 --> 00:36:09,969
Though I assure you that I shall judge only upon the evidence you present.

00:36:09,969 --> 00:36:13,109
There was a quiet authority in Holmes' tone,

00:36:13,109 --> 00:36:18,360
one that seemed to compel honesty even from those who might otherwise resort to deception.

00:36:18,360 --> 00:36:19,579
..

00:36:19,579 --> 00:36:24,820
Very well, then listen closely for what you see here is not mere trickery or malice,

00:36:24,820 --> 00:36:30,380
but the culmination of years of research into botanical enhancement and chemical preservation.

00:36:30,380 --> 00:36:31,840
..

00:36:31,840 --> 00:36:36,719
Enhancement, you say, though I fail to see how the disappearance of my servants

00:36:36,719 --> 00:36:42,099
and the terror inflicted upon my estate could be justified by such pursuits.

00:36:42,099 --> 00:36:47,079
Your ignorance, sir, is precisely why progress is so often hindered,

00:36:47,079 --> 00:36:52,719
for you see only the surface of things, while I have delved into the very essence of life itself.

00:36:52,719 --> 00:37:05,039
Spare us the rhetoric, Dr. Ellison, and proceed to the facts, for it is in facts that truth resides, not in grandiose declarations.

00:37:05,039 --> 00:37:06,079
..

00:37:06,079 --> 00:37:12,650
The scientist's jaw tightened briefly, though he continued, perhaps compelled by Holmes' unwavering gaze.

00:37:12,650 --> 00:37:22,399
The roses of this valley possess unique properties, their resilience and adaptability far exceeding that of any cultivated variety.

00:37:22,399 --> 00:37:26,650
and I sought to harness those qualities through chemical augmentation.

00:37:26,650 --> 00:37:32,929
I exchanged a glance with Holmes, sensing that we were approaching the heart of the matter.

00:37:32,929 --> 00:37:36,779
In order to refine my methods, I required subjects,

00:37:36,779 --> 00:37:42,840
individuals whose physiological responses could be observed under controlled conditions

00:37:42,840 --> 00:37:46,850
and whose absence would not immediately arouse suspicion.

00:37:46,850 --> 00:37:48,880
You monstrous villain!

00:37:48,880 --> 00:37:55,260
Are you suggesting that my loyal servants were nothing more than subjects for your experiments?

00:37:55,260 --> 00:37:58,880
I suggest nothing, sir, I state it plainly,

00:37:58,880 --> 00:38:02,420
for their contribution has brought me closer to a discovery

00:38:02,420 --> 00:38:06,199
that could revolutionize both medicine and agriculture.

00:38:06,199 --> 00:38:10,559
I felt a surge of indignation at his cold detachment.

00:38:10,559 --> 00:38:13,239
Though Holmes remained as composed as ever,

00:38:13,239 --> 00:38:16,780
his mind clearly working through the implications of the confession.

00:38:16,780 --> 00:38:26,800
experiments, Dr. Ellison, involved the infusion of iron-based compounds into the vascular systems

00:38:26,800 --> 00:38:35,239
of your subjects, thereby altering their blood chemistry, and, by extension, the pigmentation

00:38:35,239 --> 00:38:42,960
of the roses you subsequently cultivated. Remarkable, Mr. Holmes, you have deduced the

00:38:42,960 --> 00:38:48,420
essence of my work with astonishing accuracy, though I had not expected you to grasp it so

00:38:48,420 --> 00:38:58,099
quickly. It is, as I have often said, elementary once one observes the relevant data and discards

00:38:58,099 --> 00:39:04,679
the superfluous. Holmes stepped forward slightly, his eyes fixed upon the scientist with a penetrating

00:39:04,679 --> 00:39:14,720
intensity. The crimson roses, then, are not merely symbolic, but the direct result of your experiments,

00:39:14,720 --> 00:39:23,019
their coloration derived from the very blood of your unfortunate subjects. A crude description,

00:39:23,019 --> 00:39:29,320
perhaps, but not entirely inaccurate, for the integration of human-derived compounds has

00:39:29,320 --> 00:39:35,180
indeed produced results far beyond my initial expectations. This is madness,

00:39:35,180 --> 00:39:40,420
sheer madness, and I cannot allow it to continue, for you have violated both the

00:39:40,420 --> 00:39:46,250
sanctity of my home and the dignity of those who served it. You speak of dignity,

00:39:46,250 --> 00:39:51,199
sir, as though it were of greater importance than progress, though history

00:39:51,199 --> 00:39:55,739
will remember me far more kindly than it remembers those who stood in my way.

00:39:55,739 --> 00:40:03,559
Holmes raised a hand slightly, signaling for calm, though his expression had grown more severe than I had ever seen it.

00:40:03,559 --> 00:40:12,590
Your error, Dr. Ellison, lies not in your intellect, but in your assumption that ends may justify means.

00:40:12,590 --> 00:40:21,300
For such reasoning invariably leads to destruction, both of others and ultimately of oneself.

00:40:21,300 --> 00:40:28,880
self. You speak as though you possess some moral authority, Mr. Holmes, though you yourself have

00:40:28,880 --> 00:40:35,070
profited from the suffering of others by solving crimes that would not exist without human frailty.

00:40:35,070 --> 00:40:43,639
There is a distinction, sir, between confronting wrongdoing and perpetrating it, and it is a

00:40:43,639 --> 00:40:49,980
distinction you have chosen to ignore. The tension in the tunnel had reached a breaking point,

00:40:49,980 --> 00:40:54,360
and I sensed that events were about to take a decisive turn.

00:40:54,360 --> 00:40:58,119
Mr. Holmes, we must put an end to this at once

00:40:58,119 --> 00:41:03,559
for I cannot bear to think what further horrors this man might commit if left unchecked.

00:41:03,559 --> 00:41:06,039
Indeed, Mr. Ashcroft.

00:41:06,039 --> 00:41:10,960
And I believe the time has come to conclude this matter

00:41:10,960 --> 00:41:15,869
though not in the manner our friend here might anticipate.

00:41:15,869 --> 00:41:18,280
Before Dr. Ellison could react,

00:41:18,280 --> 00:41:25,360
In fact, Holmes moved with surprising surah, seizing a nearby lever attached to the apparatus and pulling it firmly.

00:41:25,360 --> 00:41:30,980
What have you done, Mr. Holmes? For you, metal with forces you do not fully comprehend.

00:41:30,980 --> 00:41:50,320
On the contrary, Dr. Ellison, I understand them sufficiently to recognize that this mechanism controls the airflow within the tunnel and that its disruption will render your operations considerably less effective.

00:41:50,320 --> 00:41:51,480
..

00:41:51,480 --> 00:41:59,480
A sudden rush of air filled the passage, extinguishing several of the smaller lamps and plunging parts of the tunnel into deeper shadow.

00:41:59,480 --> 00:42:08,139
You may have hindered me, Mr. Holmes, but you have not defeated me, for I shall simply relocate my work and continue elsewhere.

00:42:08,139 --> 00:42:23,659
That, I fear, will not be possible, for I took the liberty of informing the local authorities of our findings before we descended, and I expect they will arrive shortly.

00:42:23,659 --> 00:42:28,659
The color drained from Dr. Ellison's face as the realization dawned upon him.

00:42:28,659 --> 00:42:29,840
..

00:42:29,840 --> 00:42:38,300
You anticipated this outcome from the beginning, did you not, Mr. Holmes, and allowed me to reveal myself fully before closing the trap.

00:42:38,300 --> 00:42:53,480
It is often advantageous, Dr. Ellison, to allow one's opponent the illusion of control, for it encourages them to act in ways that ultimately betray their position.

00:42:53,480 --> 00:43:02,659
Moments later, the distant sound of voices and approaching footsteps echoed through the tunnel, signaling the arrival of the authorities.

00:43:02,659 --> 00:43:11,960
At last, justice will be served, though I cannot help but feel a profound sorrow for those who have suffered as a result of this man's actions.

00:43:11,960 --> 00:43:23,470
As do I, Mr. Ashcroft. For while we may bring the perpetrator to account, we cannot undo the harm that has already been done.

00:43:23,470 --> 00:43:34,760
Dr. Ellison was taken into custody without further resistance, his once defiant demeanor replaced by a resigned silence that spoke volumes about the collapse of his grand design.

00:43:34,760 --> 00:43:46,059
In the days that followed, the hidden tunnels were sealed, the apparatus dismantled, and the valley began, slowly but surely, to recover from the shadow that had fallen upon it.

00:43:46,059 --> 00:43:47,240
..

00:43:47,240 --> 00:43:55,480
You see, Watson, how the application of reason and observation can unravel even the most intricate of schemes.

00:43:55,480 --> 00:44:02,860
Though I confess that this case has been one of the more unusual in recent memory.

00:44:02,860 --> 00:44:14,619
Indeed, Holmes, for I cannot recall another instance in which science and cruelty were so inextricably intertwined, nor one that has left such a lasting impression upon my mind.

00:44:14,619 --> 00:44:31,420
Then let it serve as a reminder, my dear Watson, that knowledge, while powerful, must always be tempered by conscience, lest it become a tool for destruction rather than enlightenment.

00:44:31,420 --> 00:44:39,380
As we departed Rosemond Valley, I could not help but reflect upon the strange and unsettling events we had witnessed,

00:44:39,380 --> 00:44:42,369
and upon the enduring brilliance of my friend,

00:44:42,369 --> 00:44:50,060
whose mastery of deduction had once again brought clarity to a mystery that had seemed, at first, beyond the reach of reason.

00:44:50,060 --> 00:44:55,860
And so concludes the account of what I have come to call the adventure of the Rosemond Valley,

00:44:55,860 --> 00:45:02,719
A case that stands as both a triumph of intellect and a cautionary tale of ambition unrestrained by morality.

00:45:02,719 --> 00:45:03,320
.

